CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 11, 1961, p. 2, reads: "Candidates Work Hard in Victory Quest - Were for you, Henry! - Thirteenth Ward Democratic Aldermanic candidate, Henry Ryan (in trench coat), who polled 4,010 votes to win and become the first-elected Negro alderman in the ward, is surrounded by 15th and 16th District supporters. - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Women and men gathered around alderman candidate Henry Ryan wearing light colored trench coat and eyeglasses, with Mary's Market in background
